<plot>This film won best documentary at the 2003 Whistler Film Festival in Canada. It's a satirical comedy that chronicles 3 young Canadian film makers from Yellowknife as they travel from northern Canada to the middle east just as the Iraq war is erupting. As well as being very funny, it is also quite thought provoking. The trio travels through Canada, Turkey, Israel, Jordan and finally Washington DC interviewing "regular people" for their comments on the impending war.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?056485</url></doc>
